    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mechanical presses that incorporate a heating element that are used to mount drawings, prints, photographs, or other paper-based work to a stiff backing by using a special mounting tissue as an adhesive. The heating element melts the mounting tissue between the print and backing to create a permanent adhesion.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
